    "rawText": "We can either work in fractions or percentages. This solution works in fractions.\nThe fraction of red paint in P is 10\n                                  3\n                                     and in Q is 51 . Let the fraction of red paint in R be x.\nThe combination is in the ratio 12 : 5 : 3, with 14 red paint, so the composition is as follows:\n\n\n                                    Paint   Volume       Red\n                                      P        12           3\n                                                       12 × 10\n                                      Q         5       5 × 51\n                                      R         3        3x\n                                    total      20      20 × 14\n\nWe can now sum the individual red amounts, giving:\n\n                                      3         1\n                                 12 × 10 +5×      + 3x = 20 × 14\n                                                5\n\n   5 + 3x = 5, giving 3x = 5 = 40%, so x = 13 3 %.\nso 23                      2                  1\n\nThe correct answer is C.\n\n\n\n\n                                                 9\n                                                                                       © UCLES 2019"
